REFERENCE CONCEPT I LOVE:
I have seen a contact form where the HTML form inputs (name, email, checkbox, submit) are overlaid on a large SVG canvas. The SVG contains animated mechanical machines — gears, pulleys, a spray hand, a grabbing hand, scales, a car, timing chains, spiral springs, weight objects — all connected together. As the user interacts with the form fields, the machines react:
- Typing a valid name → gears start spinning, which drives a piston, which powers a spray gun that slowly paints the submit button visible
- Typing a valid email → a spiral spring winds up, a hammer strikes, a grabbing hand closes, a car launches on a ramp
- Checking a checkbox → a pulley system pulls a rope that rotates the submit button into place
- All conditions met + submit clicked → all SVG elements fade out randomly with staggered opacity

The key idea: the form fields are invisible inputs floating over a large SVG mechanical illustration. Filling the form DRIVES the machines. The machines are the visual feedback. GSAP handles all animation. The SVG is pointer-events:none so inputs work normally underneath.

YOUR TASK:
Create a completely new version of this concept adapted to my theme. Same core idea — HTML form inputs overlaid on a large SVG canvas with interconnected animated machines that react to form interaction — but completely redesigned to match my dark sci-fi space theme.

SPECIFIC REQUIREMENTS:

1. COLOR SCHEME:
- Background: #03060e
- SVG strokes: #00ddc8 (teal) with varying opacity
- SVG fills: rgba(0, 221, 200, 0.08) for panels, #00ddc8 for active elements
- Glowing effects: filter: drop-shadow(0 0 6px #00ddc8) on active SVG parts
- White/off-white: rgba(224, 232, 228, 0.9) for secondary elements

2. THEME-APPROPRIATE MACHINES (replace the mechanical workshop machines with space/sci-fi equivalents):
Instead of gears + spray gun + car ramp, use machines like:
- A satellite dish that rotates and locks on signal when name is valid
- Antenna arrays that extend/retract
- A radar sweep circle that activates
- Circuit board traces that illuminate path by path
- A waveform oscilloscope that goes from flat to active sine wave
- Orbital rings that start spinning around a planet
- A telescope that extends and focuses
- Energy coils / tesla coil arcs between nodes
- Particle accelerator ring with a particle traveling around it
- A signal tower that pulses outward rings when activated
- Countdown display segments that fill in
- A docking mechanism that locks two pieces together

3. FORM FIELDS (same 4 fields):
- Name input → triggers machine A
- Email input → triggers machine B  
- Checkbox (agree) → triggers machine C / repositions submit
- Submit button → hidden/invisible until conditions met, revealed by machine animations

4. SVG SETUP:
- viewBox="0 0 1000 1000" or wider
- Form container absolutely positioned over SVG, centered
- SVG is pointer-events: none
- Inputs are minimal — dark background, teal border on focus, teal border when valid
- Input placeholder text in Share Tech Mono font
- Valid state: border becomes full teal with glow

5. ANIMATION REQUIREMENTS (GSAP):
- All SVG animations use GSAP timelines
- Machines should have idle/ambient animations even before interaction
- Active machines should have satisfying mechanical feedback
- Connecting lines between machines should draw themselves (stroke-dashoffset)
- Particle effects along paths when machines are active
- On submit (all valid): SVG elements dissolve with staggered random opacity fade, then form submits

6. SPECIFIC INTERACTION MAPPING:
- Name valid (>3 chars) → satellite dish rotates to locked position, radar sweep activates, circuit traces light up path to email field
- Name invalid → dish returns to searching position, radar goes dark, traces dim
- Email valid (regex) → oscilloscope waveform animates from flat to active, orbital rings begin spinning, energy coils arc
- Email invalid → waveform flattens, rings slow to stop
- Checkbox checked → docking mechanism locks, submit button rotates/slides into final position
- All valid → full system "ONLINE" state — all machines active simultaneously, ambient particle flow across all connections
- Submit click (all valid) → "TRANSMISSION INITIATED" sequence — machines one by one power down with particle burst, SVG fades, form disappears

7. LAYOUT:
- Container fixed, centered on screen
- Form inputs stacked vertically, width ~270px
- SVG canvas ~1000px wide, positioned absolutely behind/around form
- On mobile: SVG hidden or simplified, form inputs only

8. CODE REQUIREMENTS:
- Pure HTML + CSS + vanilla JS
- GSAP 3 loaded from CDN (gsap.min.js)
- Single HTML file with inline SVG
- No external dependencies except GSAP
- Commented code explaining each machine section
- layoutPreparation() function to set initial positions
- Each machine has its own createXxxTimeline() function
- State object tracking: nameValid, emailValid, checkboxChecked, submitReady

9. QUALITY BAR:
- This should look like it belongs on an Awwwards site
- The machines should feel physically connected — when machine A moves, it should visually drive machine B through a visible connector (line, path, chain)
- Teal glow should intensify as more fields are completed — the whole canvas gets brighter
- The submit button should feel earned — it's dim/invisible until the user completes the form

Generate the complete HTML file with all SVG, CSS, and JavaScript. Make it production-ready and visually impressive.
